This paper deals with predicting popularity of comments in an online discussion forum using reinforcement learning, which involves natural language state and action spaces. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the categories of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves incorporating external knowledge sources and dealing with combinatorial action spaces, which could also place it in the categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
